@teachertwit2 The eCall system is not traceable and is not subject to any tracking before the emergency call is triggered by a serious accident. Vehicle manufacturers will be sanctioned if they don’t comply with EU law.
@MirceaKitsune eCall remains dormant until a serious accident happens. It's not traceable, no tracking or transmission of data takes place during the normal operation of the system.

@Swissairliner Today we will lose another 70 lives on EU roads. 112 eCall can speed up emergency response times by 40% in urban areas and 50% in the countryside and reduce the number of fatalities by at least 4%. So, we do not think is a waste of money.
